## 8. Comparison: Plugin Complexity

**Simplest → Most Complex**:
1. **Nostr** (503 lines channel.ts): Direct DM via Nostr relays
2. **IRC** (file count ~36): Chat protocol with rooms
3. **Signal** (file count ~45): Mobile messaging protocol
4. **Discord** (most complex): Guild/thread model with permissions

**Why Nostr is Minimal**:
- DMs only (no group support yet)
- No media attachment handling
- Single account model (currently)
- Passive relay model (no active polling loop)
- ~30 files total vs 45+ for Signal

---

## 9. Critical TypeScript Type Signatures

### Plugin Entry Registration
```typescript
export function defineChannelPluginEntry<TPlugin>({
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  plugin: TPlugin;
  configSchema?: OpenClawPluginConfigSchema | (() => OpenClawPluginConfigSchema);
  setRuntime?: (runtime: PluginRuntime) => void;
  registerCliMetadata?: (api: OpenClawPluginApi) => void;
  registerFull?: (api: OpenClawPluginApi) => void;
}): DefinedChannelPluginEntry<TPlugin>;
```

### Setup Adapter
```typescript
type ChannelSetupAdapter = {
  probe?: (ctx: ChannelSetupProbeContext) => Promise<ChannelSetupProbeResult>;
  audit?: (ctx: ChannelSetupAuditContext) => Promise<ChannelSetupAuditResult>;
};
```

### Outbound Adapter
```typescript
type ChannelOutboundAdapter = {
  deliveryMode: "direct" | "queued";
  textChunkLimit?: number;
  sendText?: (ctx: {
    cfg: OpenClawConfig;
    to: string;
    text?: string;
    accountId?: string | null;
  }) => Promise<OutboundDeliveryResult>;
  sendMedia?: (ctx: {...}) => Promise<OutboundDeliveryResult>;
  sendPoll?: (ctx: {...}) => Promise<ChannelPollResult>;
};
```

### Gateway Adapter (Inbound)
```typescript
type ChannelGatewayAdapter<ResolvedAccount> = {
  startAccount?: (ctx: {
    cfg: OpenClawConfig;
    account: ResolvedAccount;
    setStatus: (status: any) => void;
    log?: PluginLogger;
  }) => Promise<{ stop: () => void }>;
  startChannel?: (ctx: {...}) => Promise<{stop: () => void}>;
